p: \rWhat are you doing here? I thought you swore off talking to me forever.
\rI wanted to see it with my own eyes.
\rYou know, Darkrai! We've talked about this before!
\rListen, Persephone.\nI know you seem to think that I'm best friends with the legendary Pokemon, but I'm really not.
\rPerse... you need to get out of this cult business while you still can.
\rI get that you want revenge- so do I- but this isn't going to work.
\rYou're going to get yourself hurt, or worse!\nYou might even get captured again!
\rWow, Diana. The way you phrased that...
\rOh drop it, Persephone. It was years ago and-
\rYou abandoned me, Dia! That's not just water under the bridge!
\rIf you're not willing to help, I'm leaving.\nI'm a busy woman- people to meet, places to be, threats to the Augur to capture.
\rOh, yeah. I suppose you haven't heard.
\rI'm looking for a young girl who escaped from our custody a while ago.
\rThe Augur's scared of her... and for good reason.
\rIf I don't find her, then he's going to come after us instead.
\rI'm looking for a young boy who escaped from our custody a while ago.
\rThe Augur's scared of him... and for good reason.
\rIf I don't find him, then he's going to come after us instead.
\rSort of like the one behind you?
\rJust my luck- of course you'd appear when I don't have my full team on me!
\rBut no matter! I'll still take you out right here!
\rYou're going right back into custody... and this time, you'll never escape! Hahaha!
\rJust my luck... only I would find the very person I was looking for when I'm woefully unprepared.
\rYou better watch your back, \pn. Nobody escapes me twice!

\rI'm not going to defend her, but there is a reason why she's doing what she does.
\rIt doesn't justify it, but please don't rush to judge her.

\bWelcome to Selene City, the city that nobody likes!
\bJust kidding!\nJokes aside, though, a lot of people think this city's atmosphere is creepy and odd.
\bJokes aside, it has a pretty bad reputation because it's so creepy here.
\rSome weird woman with white hair came into town today.
\rShe looked angry and made a beeline for the Gym.
\rI'm sure Diana can take care of herself, but it still makes me nervous!\nYou never know what might happen!
\bOur city's Gym Leader specializes in both Psychic- and Ghost-types: pretty spooky, right?
\bThese ancient archways aren't very structurally stable, but we keep them up to show our respect to the city's history.
\bBesides, they do give the city a certain mystic feel to it, don't they?
\rThis lighthouse lets us look over the forest for miles and miles.
\rThat way, if someone gets lost or injured, we can find them and help them as soon as possible!
\bI found this weird stone while spelunking yesterday.
\bDo you want it? I don't have a clue what it is.
\bLet me know if you figure out what it does.
\bLet me know if you figure out what it does.
\bI won a Mega Ring in the lottery today!\nI'm feeling pretty good about myself. It's nice to be one of the few people in the region to own something!
\bI even have a Marowite, too! That way, I can use it to its maximum potential!
\b...what's this? You also have a Marowak?
\b...and you think you'd be a better fit for the stone?
\bFine. We'll have a battle, then. The winner gets to keep the Mega Stone.\nSound fair?
\bI can't believe I lost to you... but I did make a deal!
\bHere's the Marowite. I actually have a couple of them, so it's not a huge loss!
\bYou probably wouldn't appreciate that, considering you don't have a Marowak, but it's pretty awesome.
\bI can't believe I lost to you... but fair is fair!
\rI work in the Gym in the nothern part of the town, but we're busy right now.
\rDiana's talking to her sister or something. I'm not really sure.
\bI saw a bizarre creature last night, with the torso of a chicken.
\bIt was wrapped in smoke. It scared the daylights out of me!
\bHey, you! The Gym is off-limits! Clear outta here!
\rGo, but don't tell her I let you in!
\bThe creature with the tail of a snake...
\bNobody can fight it because they don't even know what it looks like.
\rI like to grow flowers as a hobby.
\rHey, \pn, I... I need a huge favour.
\rListen, after the events on Mount Rose...
\rFamily should come first. And I let fear come in between my sister and me.
\rPersephone might be the most important person in my life. Now more than ever.\nAfter, y'know... the thing on Mount Rose.
\rI'd like you to deliver this package to her.
\rI can pay you when you get back, I promise.
\rIt's something that's very important to both of us.
\rI just want Persephone to know that... I'd like to start over with her.
\rIt would really mean a lot to me. This is a bridge I'd really like to rebuild.
\rCan you deliver that parcel to Persephone?
\rI just want her to know that... I'd like to start over.
\rAll the way to the Dream Realm?
\rI... I wasn't sure if you'd actually do it.
\rThank you so much. That really means the world to me.
\rNobody's seen Calreath since the whole battle up on Mount Rose.
\rI've been looking hard, but no luck so far.
\rBut just in case... well, I think it'd be best if you take of his Manaphy in the mean time.
\rI think it's what he would have wanted, too.
\rI'm going to leave the Gym as is- maybe somebody will take over if they're ambitious enough.
\rIn the meantime, I'd really like to help out Professor Sylvan.
\rThe study of Pokemon has always been so interesting to me. Especially rarer ones, like Delta Species.
\rHelping her out has been a dream come true.
\r...because of that, I had to say goodbye to my team.
\rHonestly, I think they'll be happier off without me.
\rI definitely wasn't doing them any favours by being around them when I'm this worried about Calreath!
\rHopefully they'll be happy in the wild.
\rThank you again, \pn. I'm so glad I have a caring friend like you to help me out.
